  "A ball is thrown upward with height h = −16t² + 48t and a drone hovers at h = 32 feet. At what time(s) does the ball reach the drone?": "",
  "t = 1 second and t = 2 seconds": "",
  "t = 0.5 seconds only": "",
  "The ball never reaches the drone": "",
  "t = 3 seconds only": "",
  "Setting −16t² + 48t = 32 gives −16t² + 48t − 32 = 0. Dividing by −16: t² − 3t + 2 = 0, so (t − 1)(t − 2) = 0, giving t = 1 and t = 2 seconds.": "",
  "A firework's height is h = −5t² + 30t and a cloud layer is at h = 25 meters. How many times does the firework pass through the cloud layer?": "",
  "3 times": "",
  "1 time": "",
  "0 times": "",
  "2 times": "",
  "Setting −5t² + 30t = 25 gives −5t² + 30t − 25 = 0, or t² − 6t + 5 = 0, so (t − 1)(t − 5) = 0. The firework passes through 25 m at t = 1 s (going up) and t = 5 s (coming down).": "",
  "A company's revenue is modeled by R = −2x² + 20x and its costs by C = 6x + 12, where x is thousands of units. At what production levels does revenue equal cost?": "",
  "x = 2 and x = 3": "",
  "x = 1 only": "",
  "x = 2 and x = 6": "",
  "x = 1 and x = 6": "",
  "Setting −2x² + 20x = 6x + 12 gives −2x² + 14x − 12 = 0, or x² − 7x + 6 = 0. Factoring: (x − 1)(x − 6) = 0, so revenue equals cost at x = 1 and x = 6 thousand units.": "",
  "A park's arch is modeled by y = −x² + 6x and a ramp follows y = 2x. At what points do they intersect?": "",
  "(3, 9) and (−1, −2)": "",
  "(0, 0) and (4, 8)": "",
  "(0, 0) and (6, 12)": "",
  "Setting −x² + 6x = 2x gives −x² + 4x = 0, or x(−x + 4) = 0. So x = 0 (y = 0) or x = 4 (y = 8). The intersection points are (0, 0) and (4, 8).": "",
  "A toy rocket's height is h = −4.9t² + 20t and a bird flies at a constant height of h = 15 meters. Does the rocket reach the bird?": "",
  "Yes, at two times (once going up and once coming down)": "",
  "Yes, at three times": "",
  "Yes, at exactly one time (tangent)": "",
  "No, the rocket's maximum height is less than 15 m": "",
  "Setting −4.9t² + 20t = 15 gives −4.9t² + 20t − 15 = 0. The discriminant is 400 − 4(4.9)(15) = 400 − 294 = 106 > 0, so there are two intersection times. The rocket passes 15 m on the way up and again on the way down.": "",
  "A water fountain's stream follows y = −0.5x² + 3x and a decorative light beam follows y = 0.5x + 2. At what x-values do they meet?": "",
  "x = 1 and x = 4": "",
  "x = 0 and x = 6": "",
  "They do not meet": "",
  "Setting −0.5x² + 3x = 0.5x + 2 gives −0.5x² + 2.5x − 2 = 0. Multiplying by −2: x² − 5x + 4 = 0, so (x − 1)(x − 4) = 0, giving x = 1 and x = 4.": "",
  "Two cars race on a track. Car A's position is d = t² + 2t and Car B's is d = 5t + 4 (distance in meters, time in seconds). When does Car A catch Car B?": "",
  "t = 1 second only": "",
  "t = 4 seconds only": "",
  "Car A never catches Car B": "",
  "t = 2 and t = 3 seconds": "",
