  "A bridge's arch is modeled by y = −0.01x² + 4 and the water level during a flood is y = 1. How wide is the section of the arch above water level?": "",
  "30 units": "",
  "40 units": "",
  "About 34.6 units": "",
  "20 units": "",
  "Setting −0.01x² + 4 = 1 gives −0.01x² = −3, so x² = 300, meaning x = ±√300 ≈ ±17.32. The width is 2(17.32) ≈ 34.6 units.": "",
  "A diver's height above water is h = −5t² + 10t + 3 and the diving board is at h = 3 meters. At what times is the diver at the same height as the board?": "",
  "t = 0.5 and t = 1.5 seconds": "",
  "t = 0 and t = 2 seconds": "",
  "The diver is never at board height again": "",
  "Setting −5t² + 10t + 3 = 3 gives −5t² + 10t = 0, so −5t(t − 2) = 0. Thus t = 0 (launch) and t = 2 seconds (return to board height).": "",
  "A farmer's field is bounded by a parabolic hill y = −x² + 8x and a straight irrigation canal y = 2x. What is the area of land between the hill and the canal's intersection points?": "",
